<subSubSection pageId="63" pageNumber="64" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="63.[151,1437,752,1175]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
This widespread but predominantly Afrotropical and Palaearctic family of Asiloidea bee flies contains nearly 5,000 species (
<bibRefCitation author="Evenhuis, N. L. &amp; Greathead, D. J." box="[247,570,824,850]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" refId="ref349891" refString="Evenhuis, N. L. &amp; Greathead, D. J. (1999) World catalog of bee flies (Diptera: Bombyliidae). Backhuys Publishers, Leiden, 756 pp." type="book" year="1999">Evenhuis &amp; Greathead 1999</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Marshall, S. A." box="[581,746,824,850]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" refId="ref358584" refString="Marshall, S. A. (2012) Flies. The natural history and diversity of Diptera. Firefly Books, Richmond Hill, 616 pp." type="book" year="2012">Marshall 2012</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Evenhuis, N. L. &amp; Pape, T." box="[758,1027,824,851]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" refId="ref350035" refString="Evenhuis, N. L. &amp; Pape, T. (2020) Systema Dipterorum. Version 2. 7. Available from: http: // www. diptera. org / (accessed 30 August 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Evenhuis &amp; Pape, 2020</bibRefCitation>
). Rondani described 21 Neotropical, seven Palaearctic (only one from 
<collectingCountry box="[538,591,860,887]" name="Italy" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Italy</collectingCountry>
) and two Oriental nominal species, all from material received from other collectors and sent to him for identification (
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[654,832,896,922]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" pagination="63 - 112" refId="ref368107" refString="Rondani, C. (1848 b) Esame di varie specie d'insetti ditteri brasiliani. Studi Entomologici, 1 (1), 63 - 112, pl. IIIbis." type="journal article" year="1848">
Rondani 1848 
<bibRefCitation author="Robineau-Desvoidy, J. B." box="[817,832,896,922]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" refId="ref365947" refString="Robineau-Desvoidy, J. B. (1863) Histoire naturelle des dipteres des environs de Paris. Tome second. Masson et Fils, Paris, 990 pp." type="book" year="1863">b</bibRefCitation>
</bibRefCitation>
, 1863, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[914,987,896,922]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" pagination="24 - 40" refId="ref369792" refString="Rondani, C. (1868 b) Diptera aliqua in America meridionali lecta a Prof. P. Strobel annis 1866 - 67 distincta et annotata, novis aliquibus descriptis. Annuario della Societa dei Naturalisti in Modena, 3, 24 - 40, 1 pl." type="journal article" year="1868">1868b</bibRefCitation>
, 1873f, 1875c, 1877a). Rondani did not cover this family in his 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Rondani" baseAuthorityYear="1856" box="[413,537,932,958]" class="Insecta" family="Protereismatidae" genus="Prodromus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[413,537,932,958]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Prodromus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Twenty-one are currently considered as valid, eight as junior synonyms and one as a senior (but invalid) synonym (
<bibRefCitation author="Bowden, J." box="[543,711,968,995]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" pagination="165 - 184" refId="ref346480" refString="Bowden, J. (1975) Family Bombyliidae. In: Delfinado, M. D. &amp; Hardy, D. E. (Eds.), A catalog of the Diptera of the Oriental Region. Volume II. Suborder Brachycera through Division Aschiza, Suborder Cyclorrhapha. University Press of Hawaii, Honolulu, pp. 165 - 184." type="book chapter" year="1975">Bowden, 1975</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Zaitzev, V. F." box="[722,873,968,994]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" refId="ref378879" refString="Zaitzev, V. F. (1989) Family Bombyliidae. In: Soos, A. &amp; Papp, L. (Eds.). Catalogue of Palaearctic Diptera. Volume 6. Therevidae - Empididae. Elsevier Science Publishers, Amsterdam &amp; Akademiai Kiado, Budapest, pp. 43 - 169." type="book" year="1989">Zaitzev 1989</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Contini, C. &amp; Lyneborg, L. &amp; Majer, J. M. &amp; Rivosecchi, L. &amp; Zaitzev, V. F." box="[884,1098,968,995]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" pagination="1 - 19" refId="ref348267" refString="Contini, C., Lyneborg, L., Majer, J. M., Rivosecchi, L. &amp; Zaitzev, V. F. (1995) Diptera Nemestrinoidea, Asiloidea, Bombyloidea. In: Minelli, A., Ruffo, S. &amp; La Posta, S. (Eds.), Checklist delle specie della fauna italiana. 68. Calderini, Bologna, pp. 1 - 19." type="book chapter" year="1995">
Contini 
<emphasis box="[976,1025,968,994]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">et al</emphasis>
. 1995
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Evenhuis, N. L. &amp; Greathead, D. J." box="[1110,1432,968,994]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" refId="ref349891" refString="Evenhuis, N. L. &amp; Greathead, D. J. (1999) World catalog of bee flies (Diptera: Bombyliidae). Backhuys Publishers, Leiden, 756 pp." type="book" year="1999">Evenhuis &amp; Greathead 1999</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Evenhuis, N. L. &amp; Greathead, D. J." box="[151,212,1004,1031]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" refId="ref349926" refString="Evenhuis, N. L. &amp; Greathead, D. J. (2015) World catalog of bee flies (Diptera: Bombyliidae). Revised September 2015. Available from: http: // hbs. bishopmuseum. org / bombcat / bombcat- 2015. pdf (accessed 20 September 2020)" type="journal volume" year="2015">2015</bibRefCitation>
). In his paper on the Rondani types at 
<collectionCode box="[644,728,1005,1031]" country="Italy" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/xa0v-1feb" name="Museo di Zoologia" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">MZUB</collectionCode>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Morge, G." box="[739,909,1004,1031]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" pagination="81 - 92" refId="ref360282" refString="Morge, G. (1959 b) Die &quot; amtliche &quot; Dipteren-Sammlung von Prof. Camillo Rondani. Naturkundliches Jahrbuch der Stadt Linz, 6, 81 - 92." type="journal article" year="1959">Morge (1959b)</bibRefCitation>
listed three unpublished names (
<emphasis box="[1280,1427,1004,1030]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
nomina 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Maibach et al." authorityYear="1994" baseAuthorityName="Macquart" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[1371,1427,1004,1030]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Paxillaceae" genus="Melanogaster" kingdom="Fungi" order="Boletales" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="nuda">nuda</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
) of Rondani. 
<bibRefCitation author="Painter, R. H. &amp; Painter, E. M." box="[291,569,1040,1066]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" pagination="1 - 322" refId="ref362257" refString="Painter, R. H. &amp; Painter, E. M. (1974) Notes on, and redescriptions of, types of South American Bombyliidae (Diptera) in European and United States museums. Kansas State University Agricultural Experiment Station, Research Publication, 168, 1 - 322." type="journal article" year="1974">Painter &amp; Painter (1974)</bibRefCitation>
examined the 
<collectionCode box="[734,816,1041,1067]" country="Italy" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/dir2-q039" name="Museo Zoologico di Universita degli Studi" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">MZUN</collectionCode>
material without publishing any 
<typeStatus box="[1190,1293,1040,1066]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">lectotype</typeStatus>
designation. Except for the type material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1877" box="[513,713,1076,1102]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Anthrax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="palumbii">
<emphasis box="[513,713,1076,1102]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Anthrax palumbii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1863" box="[728,990,1076,1102]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Bombylisoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decorata">
<emphasis box="[728,990,1076,1102]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Bombylisoma decorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1868" box="[1005,1174,1076,1102]" genus="Mulio" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" rank="species" species="lateralis">
<emphasis box="[1005,1174,1076,1102]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Mulio lateralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1868" box="[1233,1429,1076,1102]" genus="Mulio" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" rank="species" species="marginalis">
<emphasis box="[1233,1429,1076,1102]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Mulio marginalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which are presumed lost, the type material has been recovered for all nominal species and is distributed among the 
<collectionCode box="[151,233,1149,1175]" country="Italy" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/dir2-q039" name="Museo Zoologico di Universita degli Studi" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">MZUN</collectionCode>
(21), 
<collectionCode box="[301,382,1148,1174]" country="Italy" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/1trn-7b59" name="Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova 'Giacomo Doria'" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">MSNG</collectionCode>
(four) and 
<collectionCode box="[509,587,1149,1175]" country="Italy" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/mvk4-k796" name="Museo Zoologico La Specola, Universita di Firenze" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">MZUF</collectionCode>
(one).
</paragraph>
